The paper discusses a reinforcement learning approach that uses non-/semi-parametric models to estimate the value function and retrieve cached values from similar past states. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of prioritizing and ranking stored states, which is a common technique in robotics (cs.RO) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper validates its approach on Atari games, which suggests that it may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category.
